getName

public java.lang.String getName()
Description copied from class: SailPointObject
Objects normally have unique user-defined names, though some like AuditRecord do not have names at all, and others like SODConstraint have names that might not be unique. The subclasses will overload the hasName and isUniqueName methods to indicate whether the name is a unique search key.

Overrides:
getName in class SailPointObject
